description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 9 MONTHS DUE TO MEET THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Acute Stroke Rehabilitation team at Ysbyty Gwynedd are now in an exciting position go be able to recruit a motivated and experienced Band 4 Multi-professional Rehabilitation Assistant on a part-time secondment (21 hours)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be an integral part of a friendly and supportive team consisting of Physiotherapists, Occupational Therapists, Speech and Language Therapists, Dieticians, Neurologists, Advanced Practitioners and therapy assistants in the delivery of acute stroke rehabilitation for the population of North West Wales. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post will offer you the opportunity to consolidate and develop existing skills and knowledge in stroke rehabilitation; working with the Physiotherapy, Occupational Therapy and Dietetic teams to support high standards of patient care and service in line with national guidelines and evidence based practice. You will be integral in delivering delegated programmes to support our stroke patients to achieve their rehabilitative goals. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The structure of the team will enable you to work closely with all members of the interdisciplinary team and stroke clinical leads. The team has strong leadership with experiences qualified therapy staff that will support your development. An inclusive team approach and excellent communication skills are essential for this post. You will be expected to work alongside other team members and independently to support safe and effective management of stroke patients. You will also be able to prioritise your workloads and time effectively to support an integrated approach in supporting the Dietetic, Occupational Therapy and Physiotherapy teams. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post would suit an experienced Therapy Assistant or someone with experience of working in stroke rehabilitation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 08/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Karl Jackson&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Advanced Clinical Practitioner in Stroke Rehabilitation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: karl.jackson@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01248 384104 / 01248 384100 &lt;/p&gt;
